# MSYS2-APISS sync project

## Purpose

Replay commit history from synced mirrors `msys2-apiss/MSYS2-packages` and
`msys2-apiss/MINGW-packages` into `msys2-apiss/msys2-apiss` on branch `upstream`.

## Path mapping

- `msys2-apiss/MSYS2-packages` -> `ports/`
- `msys2-apiss/MINGW-packages` -> `ports-mingw/`

## Base commit

First replayed commit parents `6fc20894663468a04dd4986a8b1c15a9d5ae8649` on
`msys2-apiss/msys2-apiss`. Bootstrap/rebuild reset `upstream` to this SHA before replay.
Do not rewrite the base commit from sync tooling.

## Replay rules

- Merge pending commits by replay rank while preserving git order within each source.
- Preserve upstream author name/email and author date (`GIT_AUTHOR_*`).
- Preserve upstream committer name/email and committer date (`GIT_COMMITTER_*`).
- Author and committer metadata are never collapsed to one identity or date.
- Use normalized commit message template from `config/mirror-merge.json` (`Sources[].CommitMessage`).
- Do not use wholesale `git merge` of upstream repos.
- Incremental runs must match append order of a full rebuild at same upstream tips.
- Incremental only: skip commits with committer date within `minReplayAgeMinutes` (default 5).
- Track replay and resume state with destination branches only (`upstream`, `upstream-ports`, `upstream-ports-mingw`); no checkpoint file (see [`docs/mirror-merge.md`](docs/mirror-merge.md)).

## Triggers

- Primary: mirror-poll on tooling repo (~hourly cron, push to `main`).
- mirror-sync -> mirror-merge: `workflow_dispatch` after package mirrors advance (`Notify.Enabled`).
- Expect ~1 h end-to-end after upstream changes; sub-hour timing is not guaranteed.
- Fallback: manual `workflow_dispatch` on mirror-sync / mirror-merge.

